# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Python environments
# .venv312 = Python 3.12 env for stage 04 (TensorFlow). ~2 GB.
# Rebuild it with the command in README §5 — never commit it.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.venv312/
.venv/
venv/
env/
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Generated pipeline artifacts — all regenerable by run_all.py.
# Kept out of git so the repo stays reviewable as source, not data.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Stage 00 output: the star-schema tables + re-merged wide CSV (~12 MB)
normalized_data/

# Stage 01-05 intermediates: splits (11 MB), processed CSV (15 MB),
# fitted scaler/encoders, per-stage result objects
output/*.csv
output/*.pkl
output/*.txt

# Trained models — rf_model.pkl alone is 9 MB
output/models/

# The fake-forecast run kept only for local comparison. Never cite it,
# never commit it.
output/forecast_results_SIMULATED_backup.pkl

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Deliberately TRACKED (do not add ignore rules for these):
#   BD_Business_Analytics_Dataset.csv  — the source dataset (11 MB).
#       Everything else is derived from it; without it nothing reproduces.
#   output/figures/*.png               — the 13 thesis figures (~1.2 MB).
#       Cited in Chapter 4, so they are deliverables, not scratch.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Editor / OS noise
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Thesis writing artifacts
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
~$*.docx
~$*.pptx
*.aux
*.log
*.out
*.synctex.gz

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Frontend — node_modules is huge and fully reproducible from
